<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 08 at 2:06PM CST  by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Stone,
northwestern Independence, southern Izard, northwestern Cleburne and
southwestern Sharp Counties through 230 PM CST...
At 206 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mountain View, moving northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Batesville...                     Mountain View...
Melbourne...                      Cave City...
Cushman...                        Mount Pleasant...
Franklin...                       Sidney...
Brandenberg...                    Croker...
Lone Star...                      Gid...
Herpel...                         Stella...
Lunenburg...                      Lacrosse...
Evening Shade...                  Bethesda...
Guion...                          Allison...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
